Drop -Werror from cet_set_compiler_flags and guard the test subdir.

1. larevt builds DIAGS CAUTIOUS + WERROR; under GCC 14 / C++20 (our art-stack
   standard, vs upstream's C++17 default) stricter diagnostics become hard errors.
   CXXFLAGS can't demote cetmodules' add_compile_options(-Werror), so drop WERROR.
2. add_subdirectory(test) → guard behind BUILD_TESTING (tests are off in the
   packaging build and the test tree pulls cet_test machinery we don't need).
See conda/potential_improvements.md (#2).
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -17,7 +17,6 @@
 cet_cmake_env()

 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS
-  WERROR
   NO_UNDEFINED
   EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic -Wno-unused-local-typedefs
 )
@@ -54,7 +53,9 @@
 add_subdirectory(larevt)

 # tests
-add_subdirectory(test)
+if(BUILD_TESTING)
+  add_subdirectory(test)
+endif()

 # ups - table and config files
